---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import Lead from "../../components/Lead.astro";
import NextSteps from "../../components/NextSteps.astro";
import { url } from "../../lib/url";
---

<Base
  title="Why this site exists"
  description="A short, honest note about why this site is here and who's behind it."
  crumbs={[{ label: "home", href: "" }]}
>
  <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl">Why this site exists</h1>
  <Lead>
    Hi — I'm Chris. I made this because I spent a long time not knowing that
    the thing making everyday life hard had a name, a shape, and a way through.
    I wanted the page I wish someone had handed me sooner.
  </Lead>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      I'm autistic and ADHD, and I found that out fairly late — which reframed
      a lot. Alongside that, my own nervous system has spent a lot of my life
      braced: often frozen, sometimes revved up, occasionally at genuine ease.
      For years I didn't even know it might be <em>stuck</em>, or that
      "stuck" was a thing a body could be.
    </p>
    <p>
      What's helped me has mostly been slow and body-based: somatic work,
      good bodywork and the co-regulation of an attuned practitioner, internal
      family systems, movement, and learning — finally — to go at a pace my
      system could actually tolerate. I'm not a doctor or a therapist. I'm
      someone walking this road, cataloguing what I find along the way.
    </p>
    <p>
      So that's what this is: a free, honest starting place. No products, no
      accounts, no email list, no urgency. If it helps you take one gentle
      step, or find one good next thing, it's done its job.
    </p>
  </div>

  <NextSteps>
    <li><a href={url("about/ethos/")}>How this site is funded (it isn't)</a></li>
    <li><a href={url("start/")}>Start here</a></li>
    <li><a href={url("")}>Back home</a></li>
  </NextSteps>
</Base>
